---
description: Single Source of Truth for AI Agent Specs & Docs
alwaysApply: true
---
All specifications, requirements, and documentation for AI agents
must be maintained exclusively in the `.agents/` directory.

requirements:

- Any changes to AI agent behavior, architecture, interfaces, or workflows
    MUST be documented in `.agents/` before or alongside code changes.
- No other directories may contain canonical copies of AI agent specs or docs.
    If related notes or drafts exist elsewhere, they must either:
      1. Be moved into `.agents/`, or
      2. Explicitly reference the corresponding document inside `.agents/`.
- Code comments, READMEs, and external docs may summarize, but not supersede,
    the material in `.agents/`.

enforcement:

- On PR review, reject or request changes if AI agent specs or docs are added
    or modified outside `.agents/` without a corresponding update inside it.
- Automated checks may flag modified files for review if they appear to contain
    AI agent specification or documentation outside `.agents/`.

rationale: |
  Centralizing all AI agent specifications and documentation in one location
  prevents divergence, ensures team alignment, and enables tools to reliably
  reference the correct source of truth.
